cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a novel approach for image segmentation using deep learning techniques, specifically fully convolutional networks (FCNs) and level set models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of semi-supervised learning, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the integration of prior information and smoothing, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of medical imaging data suggests a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia), and the use of deep learning techniques suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
